<br>
For all 3 item quests, each item is most often found on consecutive islands.  (I say most often because there have been reports of some dropping also on higher islands for some pieces.)<br>
<br>
For example, our quest with the teserra (which drops on island 1) has the other 2 components drop on island 2 and island 3.<br>
<br>
For the item which comes from the highest island, it usually (always?) drops off the boss.  For example, the mantle comes from islands 2/3/4, with the item from isle 4 from the boss.<br>
<br>
For this quest, statue drops on 4 (pegs), belt drops on 5 (spiroc), and honeycomb comes from boss of 6 (bees).<br>
<br>
Hope that help! To the best of my knowledge this guideline works for all 3 item quests for all classes... however it is possible that it is inaccurate somewhere, though I haven't encountered it.<br>
<br>
- Xylem, E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utrevize.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trevize</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/14/01 10:31:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: locs</span><hr size=1> I've had the girdle and statuette forever.  I'm still trying to figure out why the Queen Bee never has Divine Honeycomb.  :-p.  One would think, hmm  bees and honey.  They should always have it.  Guess I'm in their world now....<br>
